The course is a training of oral and written expression on an independent level (B2) to develop at best student's linguistic competence. Oral outcomes will concern discussions about various topical polemic issues. The course also includes practical training in written expression: the students are required to hand in a certain number of written papers and essays, which are analyzed and commented on by the lecturer. The course includes a work on individual correction on homeworkObjectives/eesmärkid:  Training of oral and written expression on an independent level (B2)Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1) can take part effortlessly in any conversation or discussion and can use language flexibly and effectively for social and professional purposes; 2) can formulate ideas and opinions with precision and to develop a subject in conversation; 3) can present clear, smoothly-flowing descriptions of complex subjects, developing particular points and rounding off with an appropriate conclusion; 4) can express himself in a clear, well-structured text, expressing points of view about complex subjects; 5) can write in an appropriate style complex letters, reports or essays which present a case with an effective logical structure.
